criterion.description: Allele frequency is >5% in Exome Sequencing Project, 1000 Genomes Project, or Exome Aggregation Consortium
criterion.shortDescription: Present in population databases at greater than 5%

criterion.description: Absent from controls (or at extremely low frequency if recessive) (Table 6) in Exome Sequencing Project, 1000 Genomes Project, or Exome Aggregation Consortium
criterion.shortDescription: Absent from controls

criterion.description: Allele frequency is greater than expected for disorder
criterion.shortDescription: MAF too high for disorder

criterion.description: Multiple lines of computational evidence support a deleterious effect on the gene or gene product (conservation, evolutionary, splicing impact, etc.)
criterion.shortDescription: Computational evidence supports deleterious impact

criterion.description: Multiple lines of computational evidence suggest no impact on gene or gene product (conservation, evolutionary, splicing impact, etc.)
criterion.shortDescription: Computational evidence supports benign impact

criterion.description: Missense variant in a gene that has a low rate of benign missense variation and in which missense variants are a common mechanism of disease
criterion.shortDescription: Missense in condition where pathogenic missense common

criterion.description: Novel missense change at an amino acid residue where a different missense change determined to be pathogenic has been seen before
criterion.shortDescription: Novel missense at same amino acid as known pathogenic missense

criterion.description: Same amino acid change as a previously established pathogenic variant regardless of nucleotide change
criterion.shortDescription: Nucleotide change results in previously reported pathogenic amino acid change

criterion.description: A synonymous (silent) variant for which splicing prediction algorithms predict no impact to the splice consensus sequence nor the creation of a new splice site AND the nucleotide is not highly conserved
criterion.shortDescription: Synonymous variant without predicted splice effect in region with low conservation

criterion.description: Protein length changes as a result of in-frame deletions/insertions in a nonrepeat region or stop-loss variants
criterion.shortDescription: Protein length changes or stop-loss

criterion.description: Well-established in vitro or in vivo functional studies show no damaging effect on protein function or splicing
criterion.shortDescription: Well-established functional studies do not show damaging effect

criterion.description: Well-established in vitro or in vivo functional studies supportive of a damaging effect on the gene or gene product
criterion.shortDescription: Well-established functional studies showing damaging effect

criterion.description: The prevalence of the variant in affected individuals is significantly increased compared with the prevalence in controls
criterion.shortDescription: Prevelance increase in affected vs. control

criterion.description: Lack of segregation in affected members of a family
criterion.shortDescription: Does not segregate with disease

criterion.description: Cosegregation with disease in multiple affected family members in a gene definitively known to cause the disease
criterion.shortDescription: Segregates with disease in affected family members

information.explanation:
7 total segregations
3 published segregations
4 unpublished segregation (3 LMM, 1 Share)

criterion.description: Assumed de novo, but without confirmation of paternity and maternity
criterion.shortDescription: Assumed de novo (parental status not confirmed)

criterion.description: De novo (both maternity and paternity confirmed) in a patient with the disease and no family history
criterion.shortDescription: Confirmed de novo in individual without family history of condition

criterion.description: Observed in trans with a pathogenic variant for a fully penetrant dominant gene/disorder or observed in cis with a pathogenic variant in any inheritance pattern
criterion.shortDescription: In trans with dominant OR in cis with pathogenic variant

criterion.description: Variant found in a case with an alternate molecular basis for disease
criterion.shortDescription: Variant found in case with alternate explanation

criterion.description: Reputable source recently reports variant as benign, but the evidence is not available to the laboratory to perform an independent evaluation
criterion.shortDescription: Reported benign by reputable source without shared data
